eval(ez_write_tag([[250,250],'constructionreviewonline_com-medrectangle-3','ezslot_5',141,'0','0']));eval(ez_write_tag([[250,250],'constructionreviewonline_com-medrectangle-3','ezslot_6',141,'0','1']));The construction work on the Menorca Residence project in the New Administrative Capital (NAC) has begun. This is according to the project’s developer Mardev Developments, which is a subsidiary of Mardev Group, a real estate investment, contracting, and urban development company. The development is particularly situated on an outstanding place on the R8 zone in front of central park on a space of 39.91 acres and just a couple of minutes from the Embassies District, Green River, Main Roads Network, Money & Business District, and Governmental District in the administrative capital. Also Read: Egypt: Construction of “The Curve” to begin this year According to Zohdy Zahran the project developer Chairperson, the project is built on a space of 17.64 acres with a residential area that includes 738 residential units of different sizes starting from 115m2 to 277m2.  The residential area only covers around 19.5 % of the space. The remaining land he says is set aside for development of greenery area, lakes, swimming pool, kids’ area, a 127 unit commercial part represented by the 8,800 square meters Mardev Plaza commercial mall, and other related facilities. The total cost of the project is approximately EGP 1.5bn eval(ez_write_tag([[250,250],'constructionreviewonline_com-box-4','ezslot_4',146,'0','0']));According to Zahran 40% of the Menorca Residence project has been marketed, with 50% of the compound’s sales expected by the end of this current year. The company has set aside different payment methods, starting from a period of 5 years to 10 years. Besides the Menorca Residence, Mardev Developments owns two other projects in the R7 zone of the NAC, including the 3,000 sqm Mall Light Sky that includes a total of 83 commercial units, 60% of which has been sold out. The second project, Asgard Mall, contains 70 commercial units and spans over 2,000 sqm, with 70% of the total project marketed.